node.statement: CASE 1a-ii CONCLUSION: For m = 4 exactly: |B intersect supp(g_3)| = (4+4)/2 = 4 = |{2,3,5,6}|. So B intersect supp(g_3) = {2,3,5,6} exactly, meaning NO c_i are in B. Then all c_1,...,c_4 must be in g_3(B). PARTITION ANALYSIS: Omega = 6 + n + k + 4 = 10 + n + k elements. B contains {1,2,3,4,5,6,a_1,...,a_n,b_1,...,b_k} = 6+n+k elements. g_3(B) contains {c_1,c_2,c_3,c_4} = 4 elements. But |B| + |g_3(B)| = (6+n+k) + 4 = 10+n+k = N. This means {B, g_3(B)} partitions Omega, so there are only 2 blocks. However, B and g_3(B) must have EQUAL size (as blocks in orbit). |B| = 6+n+k but |g_3(B)| = 4. CONTRADICTION unless n = k = 0, but we assumed n >= 1.
